{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71a7e69b-4269-4738-8d8f-46956f6307e3","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9, so you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and sync init, and `[TestInitialize]` for async init:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // asynchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(TestContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — handles sync init and `TestContext` injection (MSTest 3.x feature).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task` for async setup. Runs before each test, after construction.\n- Constructors can't be `async`, so this split is the cleanest pattern when you need both.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fb0156dc-6ac5-41d9-b222-014d15238148","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection — `TestContext` can be injected via the constructor. The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern still works but constructor injection is the modern way.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v2+).\n\nActually, let me think more carefully about MSTest 3.x features:\n\n\nIn MSTest 3.x, I can inject `TestContext` through the constructor and use it for synchronous setup, while `[TestInitialize]` handles async initialization since constructors can't be async themselves. The pattern combines both approaches — constructor for sync work and the initialize method for any async operations.","outputTokens":669,"requestId":"480F:2A85DF:83EA8E:9878E7:69FBEB5B"},"id":"d21600f4-c0c4-4a52-808c-014b4182b8a7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:31:21.032Z","parentId":"6ed314f5-d409-48d1-8368-e48076461294"}
